headline: Nokia Teams Up With HPE To Prepare For 6G Future
summary: Nokia Corp. (NYSE:NOK) signed a global licensing deal with Hewlett Packard Enterprise Co. (NYSE:HPE) to strengthen its artificial intelligence-based Service Management and Orchestration (SMO) platform. The move will expand Nokia’s automation and autonomous networking capabilities as operators prepare for the shift from 5G to 6G.
